01:30:55.285 --> 01:30:58.451
in some small way,
in the healing process.

01:30:58.451 --> 01:31:00.285
Penn State and Nebraska.

01:31:00.285 --> 01:31:02.743
From University Park,
Dave Pasch will have the call.

01:31:05.868 --> 01:31:09.118
And the Nebraska
and Penn State players,

01:31:09.118 --> 01:31:12.868
currently sharing
the sentiments of many
around the nation,

01:31:12.868 --> 01:31:15.535
gathering in prayer...

01:31:15.535 --> 01:31:17.743
for the victims
of these aberrations

01:31:17.743 --> 01:31:20.702
to show their solidarity
and support.

01:31:22.618 --> 01:31:27.326
And obviously,
an emotional day
for many reasons.

01:31:27.326 --> 01:31:29.034
A lot of Joe Paterno fans.

01:31:29.034 --> 01:31:31.743
Paterno was to pass
Amos Alonzo Stagg today

01:31:31.743 --> 01:31:34.410
for most games coached
in Division I.

01:31:34.410 --> 01:31:37.118
Commentator:
It's been a week nobody
could've imagined here, Dave,

01:31:37.118 --> 01:31:38.743
at the state college,

01:31:38.743 --> 01:31:41.577
the reach and scope
of all that has happened...

01:31:47.743 --> 01:31:49.410
Penn State!

01:31:50.577 --> 01:31:52.243
Penn State!

01:31:54.118 --> 01:31:55.743
Penn State!

01:31:57.577 --> 01:32:00.243
Penn State!

01:32:00.243 --> 01:32:03.577
Announcer: It's been
such an emotional week
for the Paterno family,

01:32:03.577 --> 01:32:05.951
and this morning
Jay Paterno went by early

01:32:05.951 --> 01:32:08.243
to see his parents,
Joe and Sue.

01:32:08.243 --> 01:32:11.034
Fearful that he might
not be able to contain
the emotions,

01:32:11.034 --> 01:32:13.159
he wrote a letter,
but he asked that his parents

01:32:13.159 --> 01:32:15.785
not read that letter
while he was there
at the house.

01:32:15.785 --> 01:32:19.618
"Wait to read it later,
after I leave, Dad"
is what he told Joe.

01:32:19.618 --> 01:32:21.618
A letter to be read, basically
giving him the message

01:32:21.618 --> 01:32:24.493
of what he means to him,
what this day means to him.

01:32:26.076 --> 01:32:27.493
Martinez keeping,

01:32:27.493 --> 01:32:29.159
and then pitching it
the last second,

01:32:29.159 --> 01:32:33.410
and Burkehead is in--
touchdown, Nebraska!

01:32:33.410 --> 01:32:37.993
And Nebraska has opened up
a 17-0 lead.

01:32:39.785 --> 01:32:41.285
We hear in the background

01:32:41.285 --> 01:32:43.868
chants from the student section
for JoePa...

01:32:43.868 --> 01:32:46.368
Female commentator:
The Paternos must be
a letter-writing family.

01:32:46.368 --> 01:32:48.118
Matt McGloin told me
that Joe Paterno

01:32:48.118 --> 01:32:49.951
sent a letter to the players,
a short note,

01:32:49.951 --> 01:32:52.243
and in that letter it said
that he was heartbroken,

01:32:52.243 --> 01:32:54.159
sorry he couldn't be with them,

01:32:54.159 --> 01:32:57.660
but he wanted them to focus
on this game and not on him.

01:32:57.660 --> 01:32:58.951
Dave?

01:32:58.951 --> 01:33:01.493
Pasch:
And McGloin fumbled the ball!

01:33:06.118 --> 01:33:09.368
( broadcast continues,
indistinct )

01:33:19.827 --> 01:33:22.159
...touchdown!

01:33:22.159 --> 01:33:24.118
Two scores in five minutes

01:33:24.118 --> 01:33:27.159
and Penn State is back within
three, with the football.

01:33:27.159 --> 01:33:29.618
...there's always Joe Paterno
on what to do here,

01:33:29.618 --> 01:33:31.326
whether to go
on fourth-and-one.

01:33:31.326 --> 01:33:34.660
Penn State down three.

01:33:34.660 --> 01:33:37.909
If McGloin gets the play off,
this'll be the final play.

01:33:37.909 --> 01:33:40.285
McGloin running around...

01:33:41.868 --> 01:33:44.868
...and it's incomplete.
Nebraska wins!

01:33:56.076 --> 01:33:57.743
- Roll for me, Charlie.
- Right.

01:33:59.201 --> 01:34:00.535
Oh!

01:34:00.535 --> 01:34:04.451
The D came out in nickel,
stacked the strong side.

01:34:04.451 --> 01:34:06.868
The O-line got no push.

01:34:09.368 --> 01:34:10.201
What is that?

01:34:11.868 --> 01:34:12.743
Hey, Dad?

01:34:14.034 --> 01:34:16.743
Listen, I talked
to Merrick.

01:34:16.743 --> 01:34:17.868
The Big Ten wants to...

01:34:19.451 --> 01:34:21.535
...change the name
on the trophy.

01:34:21.535 --> 01:34:22.535
Scott:
What?

01:34:22.535 --> 01:34:24.368
The Stagg

01:34:24.368 --> 01:34:25.660
What the hell
they gonna call it?

01:34:25.660 --> 01:34:27.285
Jay:
I don't know.

01:34:27.285 --> 01:34:29.909
I think we call Jim Delany
and-- and talk him down.

01:34:29.909 --> 01:34:31.785
- It's a panic move.
- No, no--

01:34:31.785 --> 01:34:33.702
- Dan McGinn should call.
- Yeah, you're right.

01:34:33.702 --> 01:34:35.285
They're not gonna
announce till Monday.

01:34:35.285 --> 01:34:37.076
If we get to Delany today,
then it'll be fine.

01:34:37.076 --> 01:34:39.535
- Stop.
- No, this is not where we stop.

01:34:39.535 --> 01:34:41.909
This is where we fight.
This is where it starts.

01:34:41.909 --> 01:34:44.076
- We're in the fight
of our lives for this...
- Stop.

01:34:44.076 --> 01:34:45.743
Stop!!!

01:34:49.118 --> 01:34:52.076
No more. No more...

01:35:17.285 --> 01:35:20.159
Sue :
He went in the pool
with the kids at bowl games.

01:35:21.660 --> 01:35:24.451
Paterno:
Our kids?

01:35:24.451 --> 01:35:26.451
Sue:
You couldn't have known.

01:35:26.451 --> 01:35:29.159
Otherwise you wouldn't have
let them go in the pool.

01:35:32.034 --> 01:35:33.951
Paterno:
I was working.

01:35:33.951 --> 01:35:39.451
I wasn't focused
on the goddamn pool.

01:35:39.451 --> 01:35:42.159
Sue: Joe!

01:35:42.159 --> 01:35:44.451
Joe, get in the pool.
Go play with Jay!

01:35:44.451 --> 01:35:47.785
Dad, come get in the pool.
Come here, Dad.

01:35:47.785 --> 01:35:52.326
Joe, get in the pool!
Go play with Jay.

01:35:52.326 --> 01:35:53.951
Jay:
Dad. Come here, Dad.

01:35:53.951 --> 01:35:55.827
- Sue: Joe!

01:35:57.660 --> 01:36:00.535
- Jay: Come here, Dad!
- Sue: Joe!

01:36:42.535 --> 01:36:44.909
Aah! Oh my-- Aah--

01:36:44.909 --> 01:36:46.493
Paterno:
Aah!

01:36:55.285 --> 01:36:59.535
Man:
It's a small-cell carcinoma
in the left lung,

01:36:59.535 --> 01:37:02.743
and it looks like
it's metastasized, which--

01:37:02.743 --> 01:37:04.993
It's not what we want to see.

01:37:04.993 --> 01:37:07.326
And we're gonna go at it
with all we've got.

01:37:07.326 --> 01:37:08.785
That means chemotherapy,

01:37:08.785 --> 01:37:11.410
and then, of course,
with radiation.

01:37:11.410 --> 01:37:14.660
But given the bronchitis
you've got now,

01:37:14.660 --> 01:37:17.785
your broken pelvis,
and your age...

01:37:44.243 --> 01:37:46.118
- Just leave me alone.
- Get the fuck out of here!

01:37:46.118 --> 01:37:48.285
- This is wrong.
- You're wrong, pal.

01:37:48.285 --> 01:37:49.785
Everybody's got
an opinion.

01:37:49.785 --> 01:37:50.951
What makes
yours special, huh?

01:37:50.951 --> 01:37:52.368
Get out of here.

01:37:52.368 --> 01:37:54.076
Man:
Get the fuck out of here.

01:38:08.493 --> 01:38:09.951
Sara Ganim.

01:38:11.951 --> 01:38:13.285
Hello?

01:38:13.285 --> 01:38:14.702
Man: Hi.

01:38:14.702 --> 01:38:17.159
H

01:38:17.159 --> 01:38:20.410
Um, do I have to say right now?

01:38:20.410 --> 01:38:23.118
Uh, n

01:38:23.118 --> 01:38:25.285
Whatever's comfortable.

01:38:25.285 --> 01:38:29.326
Um, m-my lawyer said
I should call you. I--

01:38:29.326 --> 01:38:30.951
I grew up in State College.

01:38:30.951 --> 01:38:32.743
Okay.

01:38:32.743 --> 01:38:35.743
Jerry Sandusky...

01:38:35.743 --> 01:38:39.326
Yeah. Um...

01:38:39.326 --> 01:38:40.868
there are a lot
of people who have--

01:38:40.868 --> 01:38:43.951
have gone through this.
I'm sure you know that.

01:38:43.951 --> 01:38:45.702
Yeah.

01:38:45.702 --> 01:38:49.326
Um, have you--
have you talked
to anyone about this?

01:38:49.326 --> 01:38:53.993
Well, the lawyer and...
I talked to Joe.

01:38:55.326 --> 01:38:58.660
Joe... J

01:38:58.660 --> 01:39:01.660
We-- We didn't really
talk about it.

01:39:01.660 --> 01:39:05.285
He said that Jerry's,
um, a good man,

01:39:05.285 --> 01:39:07.660
and I shouldn't talk that way
about a good man.

01:39:09.702 --> 01:39:11.993
That was pretty much it.

01:39:11.993 --> 01:39:12.993
Okay.

01:39:17.159 --> 01:39:20.076
And, um, do you, uh--

01:39:20.076 --> 01:39:22.410
Do you remember
when exactly it was
that this--

01:39:22.410 --> 01:39:25.201
that this all took place?

01:39:25.201 --> 01:39:28.868
Yeah. It was in summer.

01:39:28.868 --> 01:39:31.034
In 1976.

01:39:31.034 --> 01:39:32.076
Uh--

01:39:33.410 --> 01:39:37.034
Uh, I'm sorry.
You said...1976?

